@node Main "Chain_Gang - Documentation"

                            'Chain_Gang' 1.03

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  The idea of the @{"game" link play} is to move chainlinks so they combine to make
chains of 3 or more chainlinks of the same colour, the more links there
are in a chain, the more points you get. Once a chain of 3 links (or
more) is made, it is removed from the board.

  Each time you move a chainlink and it doesn't complete a chain of at
least 3 chainlinks, three more chainlinks are added on the game board...
but don't let the game board fill up completely, because when that
happens, the game is over.

  As you progress in the game, nonmovable chainlinks, blocks (movable
or unmovable) or bombs may appear on the game board.

  A Top 10 records the best scores and saves them on disk.

  Have fun!

               @{" Install and Play the game " link play}
               @{"   Features of the game    " link features}
