@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Chain_Gang" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries
are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must have at least 8
colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on a tile containing a chainlink (or any movable tile)
you desire to move, and while holding the mousebutton move the mouse
pointer to an empty tile where you want to move the tile and release
the mouse button (in a drag and drop manner), if the move is possible,
the tile will go there.

  Chainlinks must be connected with other chainlinks of the same colour.
Also, the links can only be connected with a compatible type of link:
an horizontal link can be connected with an other horizontal (or 4-way)
link if it is beside it, the same thing goes for a vertical link that
can be connected with an other vertical (or 4-way) link, as long as it
is located above the other.

  When you complete a chain with at least 3 chainlinks, it is removed
from the game board. A chain with 3 chainlinks will give you 1 point,
but if you create a chain using 4 chainlinks or more, you get 10 points
or more, as is shown below:

      3 chainlinks   =   1 point
      4 chainlinks   =  10 points
      5 chainlinks   =  20 points
      6 chainlinks   =  40 points
      7 chainlinks   =  80 points
      8 chainlinks   = 160 points
      9 chainlinks   = 320 points

  Each time you move a chainlink and it doesn't complete a chain of at
least 3 chainlinks, three more chainlinks are added on the game board...
don't let the game board fill up completely, because when that happens,
the game is over. When chainlinks are added to the game board, they may
complete chains, these chains will be removed from the board, but you'll
get no points.

  As you progress in the game, nonmovable chainlinks, blocks (movable or
unmovable) or bombs may appear from time to time on the game board.

  Non-movable chainlinks (indicated by a tile that is 'pressed down')
are just that: non-movable, but you can link them to other compatible
chainlinks.

  Two kinds of blocks can appear on the game board: movable and unmovable
blocks. A movable block let you move it on any empty space you choose.
An unmovable block (indicated by a brick wall pattern) is, obviously,
unnmovable. The blocks (movable or not) serve no purpose other than just
be in the way when they are not needed. As either types of blocks cannot
be removed from the game board they remain there until the game ends.

  Bombs, indicated by an 'electric flash'-like icon, can be clicked on
where they are or be moved on any empty tile. When you release the mouse
button on a bomb tile, 'lightning' bolts start from the tile in 4
directions and eliminate all the chainlinks that are on their path, those
lightning bolts are only stopped by movable or unmovable blocks. Each
chainlink removed by a lightning bolt gives 10 points.

  If a lightning bolt eliminate part of a chain, the connecting link with
the removed chainlink will remain, but the lone chainlink cannot be
moved. However, it can be reconnected with any compatible chainlink.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS

  3 game buttons are shown at the bottom of the game window:

 -Minimize game window: This button indicated by a small triangle icon,
                        is located on the lower left of the window,
                        minimize the size of the game window while
                        keeping the same gameboard tile size.
 -About:                Displays the informations about the game.
 -Top 10:               Displays the current best scores, the scores are
                        saved in a file called "Best10", that is loaded
                        when the game is started. If that file is not
                        present, the game creates a default Top 10.

@endnode

